author: The Wall Street Journal
description:
Tropical Storm Erin is likely to become the first hurricane of this year's Atlantic hurricane season and is threatening to hit Florida. Many Florida homes can withstand category 5 hurricane winds, but not flooding. Babcock Ranch, a town near Fort Myers and Cape Coral, has stayed mostly unscathed during major storms like Hurricane Irma, Ian, Milton and Helene. WSJ spoke with the town’s engineer to uncover the hurricane-proofing designs that help protect it.

#Hurricane #Storm #Shorts
title: Engineer Explains Hidden Designs Behind ‘Hurricane-Proof Town’
